<br>
player X has a single proccing weapon, which procs a 1000-hp DD &quot;Blast of Ownage&quot;.  The proc rate is 2% because he/she is uber (or deluded about stats' importance) and has reached 255 dex.  that is, every swing there is a 2% chance that the weapon will proc.  this comes out to a proc every 50 swings on average.<br>
<br>
player X now recieves a proc-buff... lets say Boon of the Garou.  This buff, among other things, grants an innate chance to proc a crappy 35-hp lifetap, &quot;Lifetap&quot;.  (ignore the +dex effects... remember, Player X has 255 already).  In the absence of a proccing weapon, this innate proc also fires off at roughly a 2% rate... that is, once every 50 swings a lifetap fires off.<br>
<br>
Now the question is:  Once the player already using a proccing weapon is given the proc-buff, what is the proc rate for &quot;Blast of Ownage&quot;(weapon proc), what is the proc rate for &quot;Lifetap&quot;(buff proc), and what is the combined overall proc rate?<br>
<br>
a.  2%, 2%, 4% (how it *should* work)<br>
b.  1%, 1%, 2% (how i *think* it works)<br>
c.  0.01%, 0.01%, 0.001% (verant works in mysterious ways)<br>
<br>
<br>
...any ideas? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugraalthedorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Graal the Dorf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 121<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/8/02 4:46:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2194.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Proc Stacking... Weapon+Buff=?</span><hr size=1> Proc buffs are not affected by DEX. <p><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=14686"> Graal MacBladefury</A><BR>
