Proc buffs are affected by DEX.<br>
<br>
And to the original poster, I have personally tested this situation many times.  Using our own line of proc-imbuing spells, I have noticed that casting a proc on a weapon with an innate proc lowers the chance for the innate proc to fire.  There's two ways to think about this:<br>
<br>
1.  Each weapon has it's own &quot;percentage to proc&quot; value.<br>
<br>
2.  Each proc has it's own &quot;percentage to proc&quot; value.<br>
<br>
If case 1 were true by it self, then once it was determined that a proc was going to fire, it would have to choose between the two, most likely randomly.  UNLESS case 2 is ALSO true, which would mean that the two procs would have to be compared for likelihood and then rolled on.<br>
<br>
From a personal standpoint, it is my experience that imbued procs lessen the occurence of innate procs. <p><a href="http://moresoda.com/eq/">Labiara Stankfoot - Outrider</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ualdarionshard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aldarion Shard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 155<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/10/02 9:01:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2194.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: .</span><hr size=1> thanks, that is my experiance as well.<br>
