so in other words... if you NEED that EB proc, or that slow proc, or that snare proc.. dont get a proc buff. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umurgatroyde.showPublicProfile?language=EN>murgatroyde</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 192<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/10/02 10:28:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2194.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: .</span><hr size=1> I'd have to see some actual hard data about proc buffs lowering the innate proc % of weapons.  My personal theory is that they are totally separate.  Why would another proc lower the % when crits, which operate the same way, don't?  There are too many theories that people come up with and think they see proof.  Remember when we all thought that leaving unlooted corpses prevented mobs from respawning?  What about the myth that you got more HQ pelts if you killed the animal with a dot or piercing weapon?<br>
